The paper discusses the use of neural network models for sentence and document modeling, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on text classification, which is a common task in machine learning and falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of convolutional neural networks (CNN) and recurrent neural networks (RNN) also suggests the possibility of the paper falling under the categories of computer vision (cs.CV) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
